<div class=3D"WordSection1">
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Hi All,<o:p></o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">RE: Tender Review=
 - C90306048 - Fire at 23 Mays Street, Devonport [WW-ACTIVE.FID3167762] [WYN=
NW-ACTIVE.FID3167762]<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Find below and attac=
hed the current response from Tower Insurance regarding the determinations o=
f claim # C90306048 - Fire at 23 Mays Street, Devonport<o:p></o:p></span></p=
>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">For the purposes of t=
his response, we initially address the concerns articulated in paragraph 3 o=
f the Wynn Williams letter (the concerns). These concerns which center aroun=
d the proposed scope of works being
 applied under Schedule 1 of the building Act 2004. These concerns are expre=
ssly addressed in the PDF attachment:
<b><i><u>ANZ1789 Response to building consent concerns</u></i></b><i> &amp; <=
b><u>39775 23 Mays Street, Devonport Post Fire Structural Assessment REV B ,=
 May 26</u></b>
</i>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Further to the issue=
 addressed above regarding the application of Schedule 1, we have been notif=
ied of other concerns noted within the Prendos report. I have provided Tower=
 Insurances response to those below,
 using the clause heading referencing of the Prendos report where possible. O=
bviously, many points below are also addressed in the 2 reports provided as a=
ttached. Please excuse the duplication. As follows: &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;fon=
t-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#0070C0;mso-fareast-lang=
uage:EN-US">6.2.1 =E2=80=93 Three braced walls.</span></u><u><span lang=3D"E=
N-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-s=
erif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-languag=
e:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Pleas=
e refer to =E2=80=98</span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot=
;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif">ANZ1789 Response to building consent
 concerns=E2=80=99 [Attached] <o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Apt=
os Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">&nbsp;=
&nbsp;<span lang=3D"EN-NZ"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-languag=
e:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;fon=
t-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#0070C0;mso-fareast-lang=
uage:EN-US">6.2.2 =E2=80=93 Load bearing walls, braced walls, and floor jois=
ts<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-languag=
e:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Isola=
ted components of load-bearing walls are identified as being charred as refe=
rred to in section 5.10 &amp; 5.11 of the ASURNZ
 material damage report dated 4 September 2025, and the post fire structural=
 assessment provide by KCL.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;fon=
t-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o=
:p><span style=3D"text-decoration:none">&nbsp;</span></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;fon=
t-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">AS=
URNZ damage report:
<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">[5.10=
] =E2=80=93 Charring has occurred to the timber wall framing of the basement=
 hallway above the door openings of the storage room,
 and above the door opening to the kitchenette.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">[5.11=
] =E2=80=93 The underside of the hardwood flooring of bedroom 2 and several m=
idfloor joist are charred.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;=
Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p><span style=3D=
"text-decoration:none">&nbsp;</span></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;=
Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">KCL Report: Struc=
tural Repairs<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Apt=
os Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">The charred joists a=
nd strip flooring above the kitchenette and bathroom area will require repla=
cement along with the charred internal load
 bearing wall supporting the joists over the bathroom. This amounts to three=
 charred joists and the associated blocking and flooring above, and the load=
 bearing timber framed wall supporting these joists.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Apt=
os Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Apt=
os Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Tower Insurance and i=
ts expert consultants have identified all the same individual damaged compon=
ents referred to in the Prendos report. Our
 response to the repair and replacement of those components was provided to a=
ll parties in Section 9.0 the ASURNZ Material Damage Report dated 4 Septembe=
r 2025. I will provide again below for your reference:<o:p></o:p></span></p>=

<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Apt=
os Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;=
Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">9.0 Building Cons=
ent and Design Requirements<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Apt=
os Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">The proposed repair w=
ork involves the replacement of existing building products with comparable b=
uilding products in the same position, including
 the repair/replacement of internal timber wall framing and several floor jo=
ists (not a complete or substantial replacement of a wall/floor framing asse=
mbly), the replacement of wall, floor and ceiling linings, and the replaceme=
nt of plumbing fittings and fixtures.
 This is building work that is described in Section 1, Section 12, or Sectio=
n 32 of Schedule 1 of the Building Act 2004 (the Act), thereby satisfying th=
e provisions of Section 42A of the Act as building work that does not requir=
e a building consent. Note that
 although a building consent is not required, the building work being undert=
aken must comply with the building code to the extent required by the Act. I=
n this regard, the provisions of Section 42A (2) of the Act apply for the re=
pair of the existing building,
 in that after the building work is complete, the building must continue to c=
omply with the building code to at least the same extent as it did immediate=
ly before the damage from the event occurred. In effect this means that ther=
e is no requirement to upgrade
 parts of the building that are incidental to or not included in the buildin=
g work.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Apt=
os Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#3B7D23;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&=
nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Pleas=
e refer further to =E2=80=98</span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-fami=
ly:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif">ANZ1789 Response to building
 consent concerns=E2=80=99 &amp; 39775 23 Mays Street, Devonport Post Fire S=
tructural Assessment REV B , May 26 [Attached]
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Apt=
